Three persons, including a baby, have escaped death in an accident at Oba in Idemili South Local Government of Anambra State. A middle-aged man was said to have been injured in the crash, which involved a Toyota RAV4. Four persons were on board. The Nation gathered that the accident, which occurred around 6pm, was caused by over speeding and loss of control. Confirming the accident, Sector Commander Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) Andrew  Kumapayi  warned motorists to avoid speeding. He stressed the importance of recommended speed limit or common sense speed limit, to avoid accident.